{\par \b Syntax:}\par perimeter(Polygon) or perimeter(Circle)\par
{\par \b Description:}\par Returns the perimeter of a polygon or the circumference of a circle.\par
{\par \b Example:}\par perimeter(0,1,i) returns \u8730?2+2\par If GA is the point at (0, 0), GB is the point at (1, 0), and GC is defined as circle(GA, GB-GA), then perimeter(GC) returns 2\u960?.\par If GA is the point at (0, 0), GB is the point at (1, 0), and GC is defined as square(GA, GB-GA), then perimeter(GC) returns 4.\par }